Synopsis:
   set status_hold [<text>]

Description:
   This variable sets the string displayed in the status bar when the
   current window has HOLD_MODE turned on, and there are lines of text
   waiting in the queue to be displayed.

   This string is represented by %H in the STATUS_FORMAT string.  The %H
   is treated literally within STATUS_HOLD.

Examples:
   Customizing the message indicating lines are being held:
      /set status_hold Held Lines: 

See Also:
   set(4) hold_mode, status_format, status_hold_lines; window(4) hold_mode

Other Notes:
   When lines are held, both this setting and STATUS_HOLD_LINES are
   activated.

